Tried openssl with multiple combinations, the behavior is different from the above java code and so unable to decrypt the password correctly. Christophe suggested another mechanism to talk to AAF instead of basic auth in which case this may not be required anymore. 

Proposal From Chirstophe:
Wouldn’t it be easier to reuse the X509 identity, that portal now generates on startup, as a mean to identify itself to AAF ? (that’s how it is supposed to work right ?)
So we could remove that password, key and encryption altogether from portal and reconfigure the portal user in AAF to be able to do whatever it is meant to do for portal work ?

